    • Method Detail

      • getDevices

        public java.util.List<Device> getDevices()
        Queries the server for the list of available Device entries. The results include both card printer and Console devices. An empty list is returned if no devices are found.
        Returns:
        List of devices
        Throws:
        CardServicesApiException - if a server error occurs
        CardServicesException - if response deserialization fails

      • getDevices

        public java.util.List<Device> getDevices(java.lang.String organizationId)
        Queries the server for the list of available Device entries for the given organization unique Id. The results include both card printer and Console devices. An empty list is returned if no devices are found.
        Parameters:
        organizationId - Organization unique Id
        Returns:
        List of devices
        Throws:
        CardServicesApiException - if a server error occurs
        CardServicesException - if response deserialization fails

      • getDevice

        public Device getDevice(java.lang.String deviceId)
        Queries the server for the Device matching the specified device Id. The device Id can be either the unique Id of a device or a valid print destination. A CardServicesApiException with a HTTP statusCode of 404 (Not Found) is thrown if the specified device is not found.
        Parameters:
        deviceId - Device Id
        Returns:
        Requested device
        Throws:
        CardServicesApiException - if a server error occurs
        CardServicesException - if response deserialization fails
